StoredProcedureSqlServerv2k5.name: [GetMarketAnalysisRecord]
StoredProcedureSqlServerv2k5.body:
@CollegePro.leID uniqueiden..er
AS
SELECT CollegePro.leID ,hs.[SCHOOL_CODE] AS SchoolCode ,hs.[RowGuid] as SchoolRowGuid ,hs.highschool_name AS CollegeName ,FiscalYear ,cp.PriorityCode AS Priority ,cp.BarronsIndex AS BarronIndex ,cp.NumMale ,cp.NumFemale ,cp.NumAfricanAmerican ,cp.NumHispanic ,cp.NumOther ,ISNULL(PercentQuali.ed,0) AS PercentQuali.ed ,ISNULL(NumQCPMale,0) AS NumQCPM ,ISNULL(NumQCPFemale,0) AS NumQCPF ,ISNULL(NumDQCPMale,0) AS NumDQCPM ,ISNULL(NumDQCPFemale,0) AS NumDQCPF ,0 AS NumPool ,0 AS NumAEV ,TimeToCollegeInMinutes ,DistanceToCollege ,0 AS NumFYPlannedVisits ,0 AS NumFYContractGoal ,0 AS NumFYPlannedVisits1 ,0 AS NumFYContractGoal1 ,0 AS NumFYPlannedVisits2 ,0 AS NumFYContractGoal2 ,0 AS NumFYPlannedVisits3 ,0 AS NumFYContractGoal3 FROM [MCRISS].[dbo].High_School hs INNER JOIN [MCRISS].[USMC].[CollegePro.le] cp on cp.school_code = hs.school_code WHERE CollegePro.leID = @CollegePro.leID
ORDER BY cp.[SCHOOL_CODE]
SET NOCOUNT OFF
